Barely 24 hours to the anticipated National Convention of the All Progressives Congress (APC), no fewer than six persons vying for the position of the National Chairman of the party has stepped down from the contest. Saturday Indepedent gathered that the six candidates who stepped down have backed Sen. Abdullahi Adamu, President Muhammadu Buhari’s candidate as their consensus candidate for the position. This was contained in a letter sent to the Chairman of the APC Election Sub-Committee on Friday, signed by Senator George Akume, who was also among those vying for the position. The letter signed by the Minister of Special Duties, Senator George Akume on behalf of the other aspirants reads, “May I kindly refer to the appeal by Mr President for the Chairmanship aspirants of our great party to agree to a consensus arrangement wherein our colleague, “H.E. Sen. Abdullahi Adamu is made our consensus candidate for the chairmanship position and forwards letters of withdrawal from the under listed aspirants to wit:” The aspirants who withdrew from the race are Senator George Akume, Sen. Sani Mohammed, Sen. Tanko Al-Makura, Sen. Abdulaziz Yari, Comrade Etsu Mohammed and Turaki SalifuMustapha.